4
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:43,220
忠诚问题

5
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:47,118
彼特 出版物规定第二稿周四前能交吧？
You'll have yourredraft on establishment levels by Thursday?

6
00:00:47,280 --> 00:00:49,555
这么早就得交？
You need it that early?

7
00:00:51,240 --> 00:00:53,356
我倒用不着那么早
I don't need it that early,

8
00:00:53,520 --> 00:00:56,956
但大臣见特别委员会之前得先读一下
but the Ministerhas to read it before facing the select committee.

9
00:00:57,120 --> 00:01:00,556
何况他还要记下来呢
What makes it harder, he has to remember it.

10
00:01:00,720 --> 00:01:03,678
更何况他还得理解一下呢
Harderstill, he has to understand it.

11
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:07,719
对了 彼特 大臣的华盛顿演讲是你写的吗
Incidentally, did you write the Minister's Washington speech?

12
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:10,152
是啊 汉弗莱爵士
Yes, Sir Humphrey.

13
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:13,357
不错 写得不错     谢谢 汉弗莱爵士
Splendid. Well done. Thank you, Sir Humphrey.

14
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:15,476
大臣到办公室了
The Minister's in now.

15
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:18,393
好 谢谢大家
Good. Right, thank you all.

16
00:01:18,560 --> 00:01:22,269
伯纳 大臣出差一周 你很幸福吧?
Have you enjoyed having your Ministeraway fora week?

17
00:01:22,440 --> 00:01:25,432
说不上 有些工作不太好开展      是吗?
Not very much. Makes things very difficult.

18
00:01:25,600 --> 00:01:27,955
哦 伯纳
Ah, Bernard

19
00:01:28,120 --> 00:01:31,351
大臣不在根本就是天赐良机啊
A Minister's absence is a godsend

20
00:01:31,520 --> 00:01:34,830
终于可以好好工作了
You can do the job properly foronce.

21
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:39,915
没他那些傻问题 灵机一动 整天操心报纸
No silly questions, no bright ideas, no fussing about the papers.

22
00:01:40,080 --> 00:01:43,595
伯纳 我有时怀疑大臣不上报纸
I think our Minister doesn't believe he exists

23
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:45,876
就感觉不到自己的存在
unless he's in the papers.

24
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:48,395
我跟你赌 他回到办公室 第一句话就是
I'll bet the first thing he says is,

25
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:51,120
"我的华盛顿演讲有媒体报道吗"?
"Any reports on my Washington speech?"

26
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:53,077
赌多少?     一磅
Howmuch? A pound.

27
00:01:53,240 --> 00:01:56,471
赌了 他不会问的 他已经问过了
Done. He won't because he's already asked

28
00:01:58,320 --> 00:02:01,835
从机场回来的路上就问了
In the caron the way back from Heathrow.

29
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:04,958
有进步 伯纳 坐下吧
You're learning, Bernard. Sit down.

30
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:08,112
瞧见了吧 大臣不在还能让人进步
See why a Minister's absence is a good thing?

31
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:12,239
嗯 可工作积了这么多     这好说
Yes, but so much work piles up. There we are.

32
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:17,190
走之前请示几天 回来之后汇报几天
With a couple of days' briefing before and debriefing after

33
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:19,999
整整两周没他在这里碍手碍脚
he's out of ourhairfora fortnight.

34
00:02:20,160 --> 00:02:22,993
接下来的半年 一旦他抱怨什么事没请示
Lfhe complains ofbeing uninformed,

35
00:02:23,160 --> 00:02:25,799
就说那时他不在
say it came up while he was away.

36
00:02:25,960 --> 00:02:28,713
所以才举行这么多高峰会议?
Hence so many summit conferences?

37
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:31,348
当然 这是我国立国之本啊
That's the only way the country works

38
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:35,672
把权力集中到10号 然后送首相去参加
Concentrate all the power at Number 10 then send the PM away

39
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:40,470
欧共体峰会 北约峰会 联邦峰会 什么都行
to EEC, NATO, Commonwealth summits, anywhere

40
00:02:40,640 --> 00:02:44,679
内阁秘书才能好好管理国家啊
Then the Cabinet Secretary can run the country properly.

41
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:47,513
反正 我们现在就得见他
We ought to see him now.

42
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:50,638
你对彼特写的华盛顿演讲怎么看?
What do you think of the Washington speech?

43
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:55,271
"英国政府是忠诚高效的楷模"
"British administration as a model of loyalty and efficiency.

44
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:59,353
"严厉打击铺张浪费 彻底削减官僚主义"
A ruthless waron waste, cutting bureaucracy to the bone.

45
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:02,432
"全世界都可以借鉴英国"   能证明是真的吗?
Britain can teach the world" Can we prove it?

46
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:07,549
哦 伯纳 演讲之妙并不在于大臣说真话
A good speech isnt where we can prove he's telling the truth.

47
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:11,429
而在于没人能证明他撒谎
It's one in which nobody else can prove he's lying

48
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:16,879
但我还是...当然彼特写得很好 但我有点担心
But even so, I'm sure itwas good,

49
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:21,431
这场演讲 听众是否觉得太无聊了点
but I justwondered whether it was boring forthe audience.

50
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:25,873
当然无聊了
Of course itwas boring

51
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:29,189
无聊透顶啊
Bored the pants of them

52
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:32,750
要坐在那听完 简直就是恐怖      我以为...
Ghastly to have to sit through it, I should think

53
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:36,071
大臣的演讲不是写给听众的 伯纳
Ministers' speeches aren'twritten forthe audience.

54
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:37,309
不是吗?
Aren't they?

55
00:03:37,480 --> 00:03:43,112
发表演讲只是例行公事 为了上报纸
Delivering a speech is just a formality to get into the papers.

56
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:47,273
不能考虑娱乐性 我们又不是编喜剧
We can'tworry about entertaining We're notwriting fora comedian

57
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:50,113
至少不是专业的
Well, not a professional one

58
00:03:50,840 --> 00:03:53,832
重要的是该讲什么讲什么
The point is the speech said the right things.

59
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:58,118
那为什么要公开讲呢     这很重要
But why say it in public? It's vital.

60
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:03,115
白纸黑字印出来 大臣才会在委员会维护我们
Once printed, the Minister defend us in select committees.

61
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:08,400
他总会维护我们的吧     那是有限度的 伯纳
He defends us anyway. Well... only to a point, Bernard.

62
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:10,835
因为一旦出了差错
Once something goes wrong,

63
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:16,120
大臣首先想到的就是推在部属身上
the Minister's first instinct is to rat on his department.

64
00:04:16,280 --> 00:04:19,033
所以演讲要印下来 让他站稳立场
We must nail his trousers to the mast.

65
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:22,988
您是说表明立场?     不 站稳立场
You mean nail his colours? No, his trousers.

66
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:25,833
省得他脚底抹油 走吧
Then he can't climb down Come on.

67
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:32,513
欢迎回来 大臣     你好 汉弗莱
Welcome home, Minister Hello, Humphrey.

68
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:37,708
伯纳 你不是说有关于我演讲的剪报吗?
Bernard, didn't you say there were press cuttings on my speech?

69
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:40,917
是的 大臣 我放在盒子里了
Yes, I put them in the box, Minister.

70
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:55,630
大臣 您知道明天委员会的听证至关重要吧
Minister, you do realise the importance of tomorrow's hearing?

71
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:58,189
可不是 媒体都会在场
Indeed. The press will be there.

72
00:04:58,360 --> 00:05:01,033
不仅仅是媒体的问题 大臣
It's notjust a question of the press.

73
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:04,317
这是要审查本部的未来工作
It's a scrutiny of this department's future operation.

74
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:07,836
要是我们表现得铺张浪费 或者玩忽职守
If it emerged thatwe were extravagant or incompetent...

75
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,992
我们有铺张浪费或者玩忽职守吗?     当然没有
Are we extravagant or incompetent? Of course not.

76
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:15,517
但委员会里有人心怀不轨 特别是德贝郡那位
But there are hostile members especially one for Derbyshire.

77
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:19,070
天 贝蒂·欧汉不会来吧?     唉 是的
No Betty Oldham won't be there? Yes, alas.

78
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:24,189
请您先牢记这份简报 大臣 有问题就问我
I urge you to masterthis brief and ask if you have any problems.

79
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:28,512
又是简报? 回来的飞机上我刚记住一份
Anotherbrief? I've only just mastered one.

80
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:30,910
是吗? 讲什么的?
Really? Whatwas in it?

81
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:33,951
记不住了
I can't remember.

82
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:38,910
坐飞机没法集中注意力 又是饮料又是电影的
Difficult to concentrate on a plane, all those drinks

83
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:43,076
打个瞌睡也要被吵醒     当然 大臣
And they wake you up. Of course, Minister.

84
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:46,755
您醒着确实不容易集中注意力
Frightfully difficult to concentrate if you keep being woken up.

85
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:49,514
说真的 就这一份简报
Seriously, this is the only brief

86
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:53,070
概括了人家会问的问题
with possible questions from the committee

87
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:57,028
非常谨慎适当地阐述了我们的立场
with appropriate answers carefully presented to give ourposition.

88
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:59,236
绝对精确吗?
Is it absolutely accurate?

89
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:02,312
谨慎而适当 阐述了我们的立场
They're carefully presented to give ourposition.

90
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:07,072
你说委员会很重要 不能显得我在误导他们
I cannot be seen to mislead them.

91
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:09,913
不会显得您在误导他们的
You will not be seen to mislead them.

92
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:12,878
都是事实?     只有事实
The truth? And nothing but.

93
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:15,190
全部事实?     当然不是
The whole truth? Of course not.

94
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:18,432
就说我们有所保留?     绝对不行
We tell them we keep secrets? Indeed not

95
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:19,919
为什么不行?
Why not?

96
00:06:20,640 --> 00:06:23,757
"保守秘密的人必须同时保守"
"He thatwould keep a secret must keep it secret,

97
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:26,878
"他有秘密这个秘密"
that he hath the secret to keep".

98
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:33,559
这话谁说的?
Who said that?

99
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:36,671
那是汉弗莱爵士
Itwas Sir Humphrey.

100
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:42,838
谁首创的?     弗朗西斯·培根 对吧
Who said it originally? Francis Bacon, wasn't it?

101
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,399
哦 对
Oh, yes.

102
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:47,358
怎么大臣不管干嘛都有简报?
Why can'twe go anywhere without briefs?

103
00:06:47,520 --> 00:06:51,035
以免到时穿帮
In case they get caught with theirtrousers down.

104
00:06:51,840 --> 00:06:54,718
穿帮? 补起来嘛
Trousers down Pick them

105
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:57,511
很好笑 伯纳
Very droll, Bernard.

106
00:06:57,680 --> 00:07:01,673
等会还有别的事吗?     您今天没有别的日程
Are we going to be interrupted? Yourdiary's empty today.

107
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:04,513
好吧 提醒我 那篇东西讲了什么?
Whatwas in that submission I read?

108
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:07,752
或多或少和去年的报告差不多
More or less a rehash of last year's report.

109
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:10,434
前年的? 再前一年呢?      都是 大臣
And the yearbefore? And the yearbefore that?

110
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:12,795
从1867年以来就没变过
Yes, eversince 1867.

111
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:16,270
只有些修饰润色而已 我们来看一遍吧?
With appropriate alterations. Shall we go through it?

112
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:18,710
非得看吗? 我时差还没倒过来呢
Mustwe? I'm still jet-lagged.

113
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:21,110
随便您 大臣 不过媒体都会到场的
All the press will be there.

114
00:07:21,280 --> 00:07:23,316
对 还是来看看吧
Right, let's get down to it.

115
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:28,352
实际上 主席先生 行政事务部
The fact is that the Department of Administrative Affairs

116
00:07:28,520 --> 00:07:32,798
可靠而高效地提供了
is run to a high standard of efficiency and supports and services

117
00:07:32,960 --> 00:07:36,999
政府所需一切行政工作
the administrative work of all Government departments,

118
00:07:37,160 --> 00:07:39,230
这点在部门报告中已经说明
as we've said in oursubmission.

119
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:42,153
谢谢 大臣 大家有什么问题吗?
Thank you, Minister. Questions?

120
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:44,629
欧汉女士?    谢谢主席
Mrs Oldham? Thank you.

121
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:47,837
大臣 您知道麦肯·罗德吗?
Minister, have you heard of Malcolm Rhodes?

122
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:51,233
不知道
No.

123
00:07:51,400 --> 00:07:57,669
罗德曾任行政部助理秘书 于去年辞职
He was assistant secretary in DAA until he resigned last year.

124
00:07:57,840 --> 00:08:00,798
行政部共有23000人
There are 23,000 people in the DAA.

125
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:03,918
对 而他辞职了 或者被悄悄免职了
But he resigned orwas eased out.

126
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:07,834
之后去美国做管理顾问 最近他写了本书
Became a management consultant and has justwritten a book,

127
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:10,150
这是书的校样
this is an advance proof,

128
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:15,235
其中揭露了英国公务员惊人的浪费行为
he makes astounding allegations of waste of public money,

129
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:17,595
尤其在贵部门
particularly in yourdepartment.

130
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:22,510
主席先生 我能和我的助手讨论一下吗?
Could I have a word with my officials, MrChairman?

131
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:25,990
知道这回事吗?     没听说还有书啊
Know about this? Not about the book.

132
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:29,436
罗德是谁?     麻烦精 不可靠
Who is Rhodes? He's a trouble-maker.

133
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,830
书里讲了什么?     不知道
What's in the book? Don't know.

134
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,195
那我怎么办?     打岔
What do I do? Stall.

135
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:36,954
什么打岔?      所谓打岔就是回避问题
"Stall", meaning avoiding answer.

136
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:39,680
我知道什么叫打岔
Yes, I knowwhat stall means

137
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:43,116
你连伞也不给我一把就推我进了台风眼
You've sent me into a typhoon without even an umbrella

138
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:45,316
台风中伞没有用 风会把...
An umbrella's no use in wind...

139
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:47,391
闭嘴 伯纳
Shut up, Bernard

140
00:08:48,280 --> 00:08:52,159
您和助手讨论完了吗?
Have you had sufficient consultation with yourofficials?

141
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:53,639
我...
I...

142
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:58,590
我来读读罗德先生揭露的不良现象
Let me read you some scandalous facts Mr Rhodes reveals,

143
00:08:58,760 --> 00:09:03,515
原文如下 "赫里福郡4号补给站"
and I quote, "No 4 supply depot in Herefordshire,

144
00:09:03,680 --> 00:09:07,355
"有2间飞机修理库 现为仓库"
two formeraircraft hangars used only forstores

145
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:11,752
"也由中央空调昼夜保持70度(21℃)"
but which are centrally-heated to 70 degrees day and night".

146
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:16,835
您有何解释?     这种细节问题需要事先查证
What do you say about that? I can't answerwithout priornotice.

147
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:20,515
不过有可能是真的     是真的 我上周查过了
It might not be true. It is. I checked.

148
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:24,639
如此铺张浪费 能有什么理由?
What reason can there be forsuch appalling extravagance?

149
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:29,590
要看存的是什么 有些材料不耐寒
Some materials deteriorate, depending on what it is.

150
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,758
铜质电线
Copperwire.

151
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:36,512
是啊...铜质电线?
Yes, well... copperwire?

152
00:09:36,680 --> 00:09:39,478
潮湿时可能生锈
It can corrode in damp conditions.

153
00:09:39,640 --> 00:09:41,358
包塑胶皮的
It's plastic-coated.

154
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:43,999
塑胶皮
Plastic-coated?

155
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:45,679
我...
I...

156
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:49,674
塑胶皮? 我会调查的
Plastic-coated? I'll certainly have it looked into.

157
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:56,230
他还说 贵部坚持集中采购钢笔 铅笔 回形针
He says you ordering all pens, paperclips and so on centrally

158
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:59,597
然后按各部门的需求发放
then distributing them against departmental requisitions.

159
