Perhaps it's just fora drink.

323
00:19:55,120 --> 00:19:59,033
别傻了 10号里喝一杯从来不是解渴用的
They don't ask you fora drink just because you're thirsty

324
00:19:59,520 --> 00:20:04,196
6点半我们再碰头 编个故事出来
I'll meet you back here at 6.30, and we'll cook up a story.

325
00:20:05,040 --> 00:20:09,033
是确定立场 大臣     我就这个意思
Agree ourposition, Minister. That's what I said.

326
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:36,913
请进
Come in

327
00:20:38,760 --> 00:20:40,079
你好 吉姆
Hello, Jim.

328
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:42,835
威士忌?     好的 谢谢
Scotch? Thanks.

329
00:20:43,720 --> 00:20:46,393
你情况怎样?     还可以
How are things going? Fine.

330
00:20:46,560 --> 00:20:51,350
说到特委会 那本书确实始料未及
That select committee was a shock, throwing the book at us,

331
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:56,435
但一切还在掌握中 我和汉弗莱会给出说法的
but everything's undercontrol. Humphrey and I can explain it.

332
00:20:56,600 --> 00:20:58,397
首相不必担心
The PM shouldn'tworry.

333
00:20:58,560 --> 00:21:03,554
真不知道罗德从哪得到这么多内幕
I'd like to knowwhere Malcolm Rhodes got all his information.

334
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:06,029
也不知道书稿又怎么到了欧汉手里
And who gave the proofs to Betty Oldham?

335
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:07,952
首相肯定气坏了
The PM must be livid.

336
00:21:08,120 --> 00:21:10,270
不过这可不能怪我
It's no fault of mine.

337
00:21:10,440 --> 00:21:14,115
为什么你觉得首相会生气?     肯定的嘛
Why do you think the PM's livid? Surely?

338
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:18,353
我们用常理分析一下吧 吉姆 坐下
Let's look at the situation logically. Sit down.

339
00:21:18,520 --> 00:21:19,953
当然
Yes. Of course.

340
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:23,148
我先问你几件事
Let me ask you some questions.

341
00:21:23,840 --> 00:21:27,674
在公共支出方面 首相有何意图?
What is the PM trying to achieve in public expenditure?

342
00:21:27,840 --> 00:21:31,355
当然要削减     为什么成果不彰呢?
Cuts, obviously. Why so little success?

343
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:36,514
公务员不配合?     所有大臣都想削减支出吗?
Obstruction from the service? All the Cabinet committed to it?

344
00:21:36,680 --> 00:21:41,708
是吧 至少我是     没错 但谁都削不下来
I think so. I certainly am. But no Minister's made any cuts.

345
00:21:43,480 --> 00:21:46,711
循序渐进 不能心急嘛     不对
Rome wasn't built in a day. No.

346
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:49,952
问题在于 大臣都被驯服了
It's because all the Ministers have gone native.

347
00:21:50,120 --> 00:21:53,590
不是吧?     公务员调教了他们
Surely? The civil service has trained them

348
00:21:53,760 --> 00:21:56,957
也许有一两个吧 不过我可没有
Well, maybe true... Certainly not of me

349
00:21:57,120 --> 00:22:00,829
如果一名大臣真想削减支出
If a Ministerwere really trying to cut expenditure,

350
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:05,471
他对一本揭露政府浪费的书 会作何反应?
howwould he react to a book exposing Governmentwaste?

351
00:22:05,640 --> 00:22:07,710
我觉得他会...      嗯?
I should think he'd... Mmm?

352
00:22:09,320 --> 00:22:11,880
这个要看...
Itwould depend...

353
00:22:12,760 --> 00:22:14,910
你到底想说什么?
What are you trying to say?

354
00:22:15,080 --> 00:22:19,676
知道公务员怎么说你吗? 他们说与你合作愉快
Knowwhat the civil service say? You're a pleasure to work with.

355
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:21,159
噢
Oh

356
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:24,278
噢...
Oh...

357
00:22:24,440 --> 00:22:27,989
驯兽师屋豪就是这么说她的哈巴狗的
That's what Barbara Woodhouse says about herspaniels.

358
00:22:29,280 --> 00:22:32,829
汉弗莱爵士甚至说你是无价之宝
Sir Humphrey said you're worth yourweight in gold.

359
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:35,355
你觉得这怎么讲?
What does that suggest to you?

360
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:38,318
是说我彻底失败了?
That I've failed utterly?

361
00:22:38,480 --> 00:22:41,995
你还得来杯威士忌
You look as if you need anotherScotch.

362
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:43,991
首相不高兴
The PM isn't pleased

363
00:22:44,160 --> 00:22:47,675
是因为我在特委会面前
with my performance at the committee.

364
00:22:47,840 --> 00:22:51,913
没能掩盖我们的失误     恰恰相反
I failed to coverup the failure. On the contrary.

365
00:22:52,080 --> 00:22:55,356
他不满意你掩盖得太成功了
He's not pleased because you're covering up too well.

366
00:22:55,520 --> 00:22:59,399
你没发现吗? 你在掩护公务员 掩护汉弗莱
Don't you see? You're protecting the civil service.

367
00:22:59,560 --> 00:23:02,358
首相和我千方百计
The PM and I are doing ourbest

368
00:23:02,520 --> 00:23:07,196
揭露无法削减支出的原因
to expose why cuts in expenditure are not taking place.

369
00:23:07,360 --> 00:23:11,558
你在帮公务员对抗政府
And you are helping the civil service to defy the Government.

370
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:14,029
我有吗?
Am I?

371
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:17,192
你想不通欧汉哪来的书稿
You were wondering where Betty Oldham got the proofs

372
00:23:17,360 --> 00:23:20,796
罗德哪来的内幕消息
and where Malcolm Rhodes got that inside information.

373
00:23:21,520 --> 00:23:23,511
猜猜看?
Can't you guess?

374
00:23:24,280 --> 00:23:26,919
你是说...首相?
You mean... the PM?

375
00:23:27,080 --> 00:23:28,718
当然不是
Of course not

376
00:23:31,240 --> 00:23:32,559
不是直接的
Not directly.

377
00:23:34,160 --> 00:23:35,957
你?
You mean... you?

378
00:23:38,800 --> 00:23:41,951
到底要我跟特委会说什么?
What am I to do at the select committee?

379
00:23:42,120 --> 00:23:46,113
你现在只有一条路可走 绝对忠诚
There's only one course open to you. Absolute loyalty.

380
00:23:48,400 --> 00:23:49,719
忠于谁?
Who to?

381
00:23:52,360 --> 00:23:54,828
这就看你了
That's yourdecision.

382
00:23:57,360 --> 00:24:02,275
我们得知某些重要事实之前 大错已经铸成
Itwas an errorthat occurred before important facts were known.

383
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:06,877
我保证 这种疏忽下不为例
It is an oversight that couldn't possibly happen again.

384
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:10,635
大臣 您说是吧?     汉弗莱爵士完全正确
Wouldn't you agree, Minister? Perfectly correct.

385
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:14,076
官方回答正是这样
The correct official reply.

386
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:19,268
但我几天来一直在深思
But I've been thinking very deeply overthe last few days,

387
00:24:19,440 --> 00:24:23,797
毫无疑问 特委会说到了点子上
and there's no doubt that this committee is on to something.

388
00:24:23,960 --> 00:24:26,758
浪费当然存在
Of course there's waste.

389
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:30,996
这些案例各有各的借口
And excuses can always be found in individual cases.

390
00:24:31,160 --> 00:24:34,357
但经你们一说 我认识到我们错了
But you have convinced me ourapproach is wrong.

391
00:24:34,520 --> 00:24:39,275
大臣及其公务员老是在掩盖问题 互相辩解
Ministers and theircivil servants so often coverup and defend

392
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:42,512
其实发现和消灭问题才是正途
where they should seek out and destroy.

393
00:24:46,880 --> 00:24:50,555
我和罗德先生 这本宝贵的书的作者谈过
I've spoken to Mr Rhodes, authorof this invaluable book,

394
00:24:50,720 --> 00:24:53,518
他同意主持一次独立调查
and he'll head an independent enquiry

395
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:58,071
研究政府执政问题 首先从我部开刀
into the field of administration, starting with my department.

396
00:24:58,240 --> 00:25:01,596
汉弗莱爵士有何反应?
And how does Sir Humphrey react to this?

397
00:25:02,680 --> 00:25:06,229
汉弗莱爵士与我同心同德
Sir Humphrey is in complete agreementwith me.

398
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:11,394
分工合作 是吧汉弗莱 我得说 我和他合作愉快
We work as a team. I must say, he's a pleasure to work with.

399
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:15,831
可是大臣 揭露出的事
But this account of what's been going on

400
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:20,949
和你在华盛顿说的"严厉打击浪费"互相矛盾啊
doesn't square with your speech about a waron waste.

401
00:25:21,120 --> 00:25:25,557
我是个老派的人 贝蒂
Well, I'm an old-fashioned sort of chap, Betty,

402
00:25:26,680 --> 00:25:29,478
我信仰一种叫做"忠诚"的东西
and I believe in a thing called loyalty.

403
00:25:29,640 --> 00:25:35,590
内部矛盾内部解决 不可外扬 对吧 汉弗莱?
Whateveryou say in private you defend in public, eh, Humphrey?

404
00:25:35,760 --> 00:25:38,911
这样的话 你现在不就不忠诚了吗?
In that case, aren't you being disloyal now?

405
00:25:40,280 --> 00:25:43,636
非也 我认为大臣的忠诚水准更高
No. I believe a Minister has a higher loyalty.

406
00:25:43,800 --> 00:25:46,473
效忠国会 效忠国家
A loyalty to Parliament and the nation.

407
00:25:47,160 --> 00:25:50,675
为这种高于一切的忠诚
And that loyalty must be paramount,

408
00:25:50,840 --> 00:25:53,434
他必须披荆斩棘 一往无前
howeverhard and painful that may be.

409
00:25:53,600 --> 00:25:57,115
我当然要忠于我的部门和部属
Of course, one is loyal to one's department and officials,

410
00:25:57,280 --> 00:26:01,831
只要证据允许 但我要公开表明我的一贯态度
until the evidence is overwhelming, but I must say in public,

411
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:05,072
改革可行 并即将进行
that reforms can and will take place,

412
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:10,439
相信汉弗莱爵士必将成为我忠诚的战友
and I know I shall find in Sir Humphrey my staunchest ally.

413
00:26:10,600 --> 00:26:12,830
对吧 汉弗莱?
Isn't that so, Humphrey?

414
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:14,319
是的 大臣
Yes, Minister.

415
00:26:15,080 --> 00:26:16,399
是的 大臣
Yes, Minister.

416
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:20,233
多亏您了 大臣     我尽力而为
A big help I did my best.

417
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:24,279
尽力保您自己吧 这就是您的"团结"? 可笑
The best foryourself This is your idea of teamwork? Amusing

418
00:26:24,440 --> 00:26:26,829
我必须这么做     必须怎么做?
I had to do it. Had to do what?

419
00:26:27,840 --> 00:26:30,479
主动向特委会检讨一切?
Cravenly admit everything to them?

420
00:26:30,640 --> 00:26:33,712
您不知道我们要遭殃了吗?
Don't you realise how calamitous this is forus?

421
00:26:33,880 --> 00:26:37,429
不会都遭殃吧 我希望      没希望的 大臣
Not both of us, I hope. You hope in vain.

422
00:26:37,600 --> 00:26:41,070
部员们全副武装 没人还信任您
We're up in arms, with very little confidence in you.

423
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:44,277
至于10号 我都不敢想
As for Number 10, I shudderto think

424
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:48,274
对您的公开检讨 首相会作何反应
how the PM will react to yourpublic admission of failure.

425
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:51,512
首相写来的私人信件
A personal letter from the Prime Minister.

426
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:56,314
我警告过您了 大臣
I did warn you, Minister.

427
00:26:56,480 --> 00:26:59,199
伯纳 你可以考虑为大臣
Bernard, you should give some thought

428
00:26:59,360 --> 00:27:03,797
拟一封体面的辞呈了
to drafting a face-saving letter of resignation forthe Minister.

429
00:27:05,680 --> 00:27:07,875
"亲爱的吉姆"
"Dear Jim..."

430
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:10,076
"亲爱的吉姆"?
"Dear Jim"?

431
00:27:11,440 --> 00:27:14,750
"我们最近没能常常见面"
"We haven't seen enough of each other lately.

432
00:27:14,920 --> 00:27:18,071
"你周日有空来我乡间别墅用个午餐吗?"
Are you free for lunch at Chequers on Sunday?

433
00:27:18,240 --> 00:27:23,314
"家庭聚餐 带上老婆孩子 期待你的到来"
We shall just be the family. I look forward to seeing you".

434
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:25,672
我不明白...?
I don't think I?

435
00:27:27,520 --> 00:27:29,556
有回报了 有回报了
It has paid off

436
00:27:30,520 --> 00:27:33,796
阴谋 和斯宾塞喝酒的那一次
A conspiracy That drink with Mark Spencer

437
00:27:33,960 --> 00:27:36,918
"常常见面...乡间别墅午餐..."
"...not seen enough... Lunch at Chequers..."

438
00:27:37,080 --> 00:27:41,392
看 还是手写的 你知道值多少钱吗?
It's hand-written Do you realise howmuch it's worth?

439
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:44,950
现价好像是30枚银币(犹大出卖耶稣的价钱)
I believe the going rate is thirty pieces of silver

440
00:27:45,960 --> 00:27:50,158
不 汉弗莱 忠诚和正直得到了应有的回报
No. Loyalty and integrity have received theirjust rewards.

441
00:27:50,320 --> 00:27:51,469
忠诚?
Loyalty?

442
00:27:52,280 --> 00:27:57,195
汉弗莱 我支持你 就像你一贯支持我的那样
I have backed you up as you have always backed me up

443
00:27:57,360 --> 00:27:58,713
不是吗?
Isn't that so?

444
00:28:00,360 --> 00:28:02,920
不好意思 你说什么?
Sorry? Did you say something?

445
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:05,911
我想他说的是 "是 大臣"
I think he said, "Yes, Minister".

